node.text:
Say “Hello! 👋🏼” to spring and “Bye!” to winter with @mandysmunchkins_’ creative, spring-inspired math projects that you can do with the kiddos at home! .

Get your construction paper, markers, and math cap ready… and GO! Make sure to tag us at @childrensplace with your photos and videos in your IG stories. We’re taking notes and will share our favorites! ✏️

node.title: Fun At-Home Activity: Spring-Inspired Math Projects

node.text:
Looking for a fun at-home activity? We teamed up with @mandysmunchkins_ to share a fun recycling-inspired tutorial you can do with your kids at home! 
Did you know? Every year, an estimated 8 million tons of plastic end up in the ocean. 
If you’ve made your very own Water Bottle Wind Spiral - make sure to tag us at @childrensplace with your photos and videos in your IG stories. We’ll share some of our favorites! 🙂

node.title: Fun At-Home Activity: Water Bottle Wind Spirals
